<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<tr><td align="center"> <h2>  Legions</h2></td></tr>

<tr><td> <a href="index.cfm?fuseaction=dsp_legion&legion=1" class="right_link"> Legion 1: Levels 11-20</a></td></tr>
<tr><td> <a href="index.cfm?fuseaction=dsp_legion&legion=2" class="right_link">Legion 2: Levels 21-30</a></td></tr>
<tr><td> <a href="index.cfm?fuseaction=dsp_legion&legion=3" class="right_link">Legion 3: Levels 31-45</a></td></tr>
<tr><td> <a href="index.cfm?fuseaction=dsp_legion&legion=4" class="right_link">Legion 4: Levels 46-55</a></td></tr>
<tr><td> <a href="index.cfm?fuseaction=dsp_legion&legion=5" class="right_link">Legion 5: Levels 56-65</a></td></tr>
<td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>Click above to see Legion Rosters</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>

There will be no Legion for levels 1-10 as with the changes to early level 
game play these levels go by very fast.
</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>
Legion Leaders will volunteer from within the ranks of the Legion and in the 
case of more than one volunteer they will be voted on by the current members 
of that Legion. Legion Leaders are responsible for the planning of events 
and assisting their members in learning to work as a team.
</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>
Legion planned raids and groups will follow the guild's raid and loot rules. 
A Legion planned raid may include more than 1 Legion and Legion Leaders are 
encouraged to work together on joint Legion raids and to help each other 
with the planning of raids.
</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>
Legion Names will also be suggested and voted on by the members of the 
Legion. When a Leader levels out of the Legion and a new Leader is elected 
the members have the right to vote to keep the current name or to change it 
at that time.
</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td>
Members will automatically be moved from one Legion Roster to the next as 
they update their level(s) in the character biography screen so it is 
important that members update their level(s) to ensure they are in the 
correct Legion(s).
</td></tr></table>

	





                </td>
			  </tr>
			 </table>
		</td>
